  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Prepare your puff pastry</strong></span></p>\n<p>Set the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 400°F/ <span class=\"text-highlight\">Gas 6.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Unwrap the <strong>puff pastry </strong>and cut it into 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> squares.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Using a sharp knife, score a 1cm border around each square.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Using a fork, prick inside the border.</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Cook your pastry squares</strong></span></p>\n<p>Transfer the <strong>pastry squares</strong> to one side of a baking tray.</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 15 minutes or until golden.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Make your balsamic dressing </strong></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Meanwhile, mix the<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>balsamic dressing</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Slice the <strong>brie</strong> through the equator (as though slicing a bread roll) so you are left with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> round halves.</span></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Prepare the other ingredients</strong></span></p>\n<p>Strip the <strong>thyme</strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>leaves</strong></span> from their stems and chop the leaves very<span class=\"text-highlight\"> finely. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Peel and crush (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong> finely.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Slice the <strong>petit pain sourdough roll<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Chop the <strong>walnuts</strong> roughly.</span></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1868.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Finish your pastry squares</strong></span></p>\n<p>Once the <strong>pastry</strong> is golden, remove it from <span class=\"text-highlight\">the oven.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Using the back of a spoon, carefully flatten the middle of each square, so you are left with a puffed-up border.</span></p>",
