      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Prepare the garlic &amp; thyme crostini</strong></span></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>chopped thyme</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> to a bowl with 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>salt</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Turn the <strong>pain slices</strong> in the <strong>garlic </strong>and<strong> thyme oil</strong> and add them to a second baking tray. </span></p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 6-7 <span class=\"text-highlight\">minutes or until the pain slices are toasted – these are your <strong>garlic &amp; thyme crostini</strong>.</span></p>\n<p>Tip: if your crostini are feeling greasy drain them on kitchen<span class=\"text-highlight\"> paper. </span></p>",
